<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CAB: 5000, 9100, 9200, 9300, 9400 - REMOVE AND INSTALL -
        WIPER ARM (ROOF MOUNTED AIR WINDSHIELD WIPERS, OPTIONAL AFTER JULY 1992)
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>WIPER ARM (ROOF MOUNTED AIR WINDSHIELD WIPERS, OPTIONAL AFTER JULY 1992)</title>
        <svcsubproc id="x1600502">
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With the windshield wipers off and in the park position, disconnect washer hose (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600589">Item 1, Figure 89</hotlnk>) at the washer fitting (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600589">Item 2, Figure 89</hotlnk>) on the cab roof.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove acorn nut and lockwasher (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600590">Items 4 and 5, Figure 90</hotlnk>) securing wiper arm and blade (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600590">Item 3, Figure 90</hotlnk>) to serrated drive bushing (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600590">Item 6, Figure 90</hotlnk>) and remove wiper arm and blade.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1600589" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg16/G1600579.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="300"/>
                <caption>Figure 89. Disconnect Washer Hose at Washer Fitting</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>A. 1 INCH (25.4 MM)</callout1>
                    <callout1>1. WASHER HOSE</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. WASHER FITTING</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. WEATHER SEAL</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f1600590" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg16/G1600580.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="300"/>
                <caption>Figure 90. Wiper Arm Assembly</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. WIPER MOTOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. MOTOR MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. WIPER ARM AND BLADE</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. LOCKWASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. ACORN NUT 54 TO 62 IN-LBS. (6 TO 7 NM)</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. SERRATED DRIVE BUSHING</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. WEATHER SEAL</callout1>
                    <callout1>8. HEX LOCK NUT</callout1>
                    <callout1>9. OUTER SPACER</callout1>
                    <callout1>10. LEATHER FLAT WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>11. INNER SPACER</callout1>
                    <callout1>12. WIPER MOTOR SHAFT</callout1>
                    <callout1>13. BOLT, LOCKWASHER AND NUT, 40 TO 62 IN-LBS. (4.5 TO 7 NM)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc id="x160052a">
            <title>Install</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the wiper arm and blade in place on the serrated drive bushing so the park
                    position of the blade pivot, the point at which the dimension is measured, is 1 inch (25.4 mm) below
                    the weather seal and push the wiper arm and blade onto the serrated drive bushing.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the lockwasher and acorn nut and tighten to 54 to 62 in-lbs. (6 to 7 Nm).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect washer hose to washer fitting on the cab roof.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check wiper and washer operation.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
